Bonomi Seeks Management Role in Popolare Milano, Sole Reports

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-09-25T09:35:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/bonomi-seeks-management-role-in-popolare-milano-sole-reports.html
Andrea Bonomi, chairman of European
buyout firm Investindustrial SpA, wants a management role if he
invests in  Banca Popolare di Milano Scarl (PMI) ,  Il Sole 24 Ore
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Bonomi is scheduled to meet Italian unions in coming days
to present a plan for the bank, according to the newspaper.
Bonomi would be an alternative to Banca Profilo SpA Chairman
Matteo Arpe, who is willing to invest 200 million euros ($269
million), Il Sole reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  